objectives.en:
Management of critically ill is the most important part of emergency medicine. The recognition, differential diagnosis and primary treatment of the critically ill patient is at main focus of the course. The aim is to teach: 
1) organisation of emergency medicine, including patient triage principles; 
2) management of  life-threatening syndromes (shock, acute respiratory failure, acute renal failure acute, cardiac arrhythmias, sepsis, and coma);
3) principles of emergency surgery, including trauma.

learning_outcomes.en:
After the course the student:
-  is able to recognize critical illness of the patient;
-  is able perform primary management of critical conditions;
-  knows the organisation of emergency medicine, including triage at emergency
   department;
-  knows the primary management principles of severe trauma in hospital;
-  knows the principles of emergency surgery;
-  recognizes life-threatening arrhythmias and is able to treat them;
-  is able to perform cardio-pulmonary resuscitation of an adult;
-  is able to present the case history in short and concise way.

learning_outcomes.et:
Õppeaine läbinud üliõpilane  
-  tunneb ära kriitilises seisundis haige;
-  oskab kriitilises seisundis haige esmast käsitlust;
-  orienteerub erakorralise meditsiini korralduses, tunneb erakorralise meditsiini osakonna
    haigete triaaži põhimõtteid;
-  teab raske trauma haige esmast käsitlust statsionaaris;
-  tunneb erakorralise kirurgilise haige käsitluse põhimõtteid;
-  suudab eristada eluohtlikke südame rütmihäireid ning neid ravida;
-  oskab täiskasvanute elustamisvõtteid (kaudne südamemassaaž, vabade  
    hingamisteede tagamine, südame defibrillatsioon, ravimite manustamine);
-  suudab korrektselt esitada lühikokkuvõtte haigusloost.
